[4] USA (Illinois, Cook County): travel associated
Date: Mon 23 Jul 2018 5:45 pm
Source: Chicago Tonight [edited]
https://chicagotonight.wttw.com/2018/07/23/cook-county-officials-report-measles-exposure-city-suburbs


Cook County Department of Public Health officials are reporting a confirmed case of measles in a Cook County resident who recently traveled to another country with ongoing measles transmission and no prior immunity to measles.

The resident also visited a restaurant and grocery store in the area earlier this month [July 2018].

[See URL above for locations visited by infected individual.] Anyone who visited those locations during that timeframe who is experiencing symptoms of measles should call their health care provider and contact their local health department, officials say. Symptoms, which can develop up to 21 days after exposure, include rash, high fever, cough, runny nose, and red, watery eyes.

Officials are working with both establishments to contact employees who were present during potential exposure times. There is no ongoing risk of transmission at either location. ...-more

[Byline: Kristen Thometz]

