[7] Ukraine
Date: Tue 24 Jul 2018 23:29
Source: Ukrinform [edited]
https://www.ukrinform.net/rubric-emergencies/2504584-health-ministry-another-child-dies-of-measles-in-ukraine.html


A total of 882 people have fallen ill with measles in Ukraine over the past week [week of Sun 15 Jul 2018], one child has died of complications from the disease, the Public Health Center of the Health Ministry of Ukraine reports.

"Since the start of the year [2018], 24 027 people have contracted measles: 9682 adults and 14 345 children. Also, 12 people have died of complications from the disease: 8 children and 4 adults," reads the report.

"Up to 882 people fell ill with measles over the 29th week of 2018: 369 adults and 413 children, which is 3.1 percent more compared with the previous week... Also, a 21-month-old toddler died of complications from the disease in Kyiv region. Since the start of the year [2018], 13 people have died of complications from measles: 9 children and 4 adults," reads the report.

Since the start of the year [2018], 26 692 people have contracted measles: 10 800 adults and 15 892 children.

The largest number of cases of measles was recorded in Lviv region (4989 people: 1568 adults and 3421 children), Zakarpattia region (2890 people: 537adults and 2353 children), Ivano-Frankivsk region (2596 people: 744 adults and 1852children), Odesa region (2063 people: 1028 adults and 1035 children), the city of Kyiv (1854 people: 1139 adults and 715 children) and Ternopil region (1388people: 540 adults and 848 children).

